WEBVTT

00:00.066 --> 00:04.013
The blueprints are drafted, the workers are set.

00:05.756 --> 00:07.258
It's time to build his church.

00:08.220 --> 00:12.267
Our knees need to hit the ground in prayer before a shovel does.

00:13.349 --> 00:17.796
Our hands need to be raised in worship before they swing a hand.

00:19.239 --> 00:23.566
Let this church be more than a fellowship, more than a building.

00:23.586 --> 00:25.970
Let this church be a house of gold.

00:28.226 --> 00:29.088
Amen, amen.

00:29.248 --> 00:30.450
Once again, thanks for being here.

00:30.590 --> 00:35.078
If you are a guest today, help us get to know you at Encounter Church.

00:35.118 --> 00:39.947
That's one of our hearts desire is that we can walk side by side with one another.

00:39.987 --> 00:46.058
In fact, we say it all the time at Encounter Church, nobody walks alone, but we can only walk with you if we know you.

00:46.098 --> 00:49.905
So help us get to know you, catch me in the lobby, introduce yourself.

00:50.165 --> 00:51.528
I would greatly appreciate that.

00:51.548 --> 00:52.850
And those that are watching

00:52.930 --> 00:55.334
online help us get to know you as well.

00:55.754 --> 01:07.613
I know not always will we see you in person but we can certainly get to know you virtually so do me a favor get your information on the screen reach out to us help us connect with you as well.

01:08.013 --> 01:21.234
All right well we are right in the middle smack dab in the middle of a series that we've been in for three weeks now and we have two more weeks to go a series that we're simply calling a house

01:21.538 --> 01:33.782
of prayer as I was preparing for this year and I was last fall I was sitting in my office and I was praying and I was contemplating I was researching and I was getting everything squared away for the year.

01:33.822 --> 01:39.794
I really felt that the theme for the year and as we've already talked about is build his church.

01:39.906 --> 01:50.325
Now, we are going to physically, in just a couple of months, stick a backhoe in the ground and we're going to begin to construct an incredible building for the cause of Christ.

01:50.566 --> 01:55.815
But if we don't do anything on the inside, then all we're doing is building a building.

01:56.857 --> 02:03.730
Truth be told, if we don't build inside, if we don't let God do the work in our lives and

02:03.842 --> 02:11.413
in the lives of the body of believers, then nothing that we do on this building will make an impact for the cause of Christ.

02:11.674 --> 02:17.983
However, if we will begin to do the work on the inside, come on, that's one of our missions, right?

02:18.083 --> 02:26.496
Love, reach, empower, that reach portion is we reach up to heaven personally, we reach in and we do the work on the inside.

02:26.516 --> 02:28.219
That's not always the part that we like.

02:29.080 --> 02:33.106
Come on, how many of you love it when somebody points out something you've done wrong?

02:35.042 --> 02:37.385
No, not a single person in this room.

02:37.605 --> 02:40.509
I mean, somebody walks up and goes, man, you didn't do this, right?

02:40.529 --> 02:42.992
I'd be like, come on.

02:43.012 --> 02:43.293
Right?

02:43.873 --> 02:44.434
Square up.

02:44.554 --> 02:45.075
Let's go.

02:45.435 --> 02:47.558
We don't like him if somebody points out wrong.

02:47.798 --> 02:52.745
But sometimes, okay, many times in our spiritual lives, there are things that are going on.

02:52.785 --> 03:00.114
There are things that we need to allow God to not only surface in us, but give us the boldness to deal with.

03:00.930 --> 03:15.090
And the only way that we can truly hear the heart of God, the only way that we can truly come to the place that we understand what He has for us and what needs to happen in our lives is to truly become a house of prayer.

03:15.746 --> 03:19.934
I'm not just talking about the body of believers as a whole.

03:20.355 --> 03:24.583
Oh, we can easily say that encountered church values prayer.

03:24.663 --> 03:26.466
I mean, it's one of our core values.

03:26.947 --> 03:29.291
We value prayer, not mere chatter.

03:29.592 --> 03:32.818
We dedicate a service every week.

03:32.898 --> 03:38.846
To prayer, we kick off the year every year with 21 days of prayer and fasting.

03:38.946 --> 03:46.195
We could say, and we could build a case for the fact that encounter church is a house of prayer.

03:47.116 --> 04:01.394
However, if all it is is information on a page, writing on prints on the walls, if all it is is details on the website,

04:02.306 --> 04:08.153
But it's not happening on the inside that it's nothing more than words.

04:10.115 --> 04:21.489
I believe that God has called us as a people to not just say we believe in prayer, but to be a people of prayer.

04:22.550 --> 04:29.719
Over the last couple of weeks, we've looked at a couple topics that really I think are vitally important questions for us to ask.

04:29.979 --> 04:32.082
Number one is, do I have to pray?

04:32.674 --> 04:33.335
Do you remember that?

04:33.395 --> 04:34.237
That was week one.

04:34.517 --> 04:38.423
We process through the fact that really that's probably not the best question.

04:38.824 --> 04:45.495
The best question is probably why wouldn't we pray when the opportunity is being given to us?

04:46.276 --> 04:56.914
You see, when Jesus died on the cross, the Bible says that the veil was torn from the top to the bottom, giving us entry in to the very presence of God.

04:57.538 --> 05:03.466
Again, we no longer need a third party to petition heaven for us.

05:03.566 --> 05:11.057
We can now boldly, as we've read in the Word of God, boldly come into the throne room of God.

05:11.217 --> 05:14.101
I want you to know church, that's good news.

05:15.844 --> 05:17.907
Let me say it to this side, because this side got excited.

05:17.927 --> 05:18.868
This side was a little quiet.

05:19.369 --> 05:22.213
I want you to know today that that's good news.

05:22.994 --> 05:25.938
We don't have to, you still weren't very excited with that.

05:26.466 --> 05:29.009
I'm gonna give them one more chance.

05:29.249 --> 05:30.511
Let's give them one more chance.

05:31.232 --> 05:33.975
I believe this morning that that's good news.

05:35.036 --> 05:36.979
Hey, come on now.

05:37.239 --> 05:40.923
You guys are on the ball that caffeine's starting to kick in is working through the veins.

05:41.905 --> 05:53.959
But when we give it to God, when we truly personally come into the throne room of God, it gives us an opportunity, an opportunity to know the very heart of God.

05:54.580 --> 05:56.402
You see, sometimes we,

05:56.482 --> 06:00.111
We don't go to God because we're afraid of what he'll say.

06:03.239 --> 06:07.791
We're afraid that his way is not our way.

06:07.811 --> 06:10.418
Can I just tell you straight up, his way's not your way?

06:11.682 --> 06:13.284
His way is far beyond your way.

06:13.324 --> 06:17.249
His thoughts are beyond anything you could ever imagine in your mind.

06:17.489 --> 06:20.993
God holds in His hand the solution to everything in life.

06:21.054 --> 06:26.520
And all that He desires is that we, His people will boldly come into His presence.

06:26.841 --> 06:28.182
We'll step before Him.

06:28.383 --> 06:29.444
We'll petition Him.

06:29.624 --> 06:33.969
We'll lay that care, that concern, that anxiety at His feet.

06:34.090 --> 06:35.371
He's kind of like our dad.

06:35.391 --> 06:37.494
He's there ready to lift us up.

06:37.774 --> 06:39.216
I know, here's the deal.

06:39.636 --> 06:40.978
When my kids were little,

06:41.634 --> 06:52.468
If they walked up with those little kid eyes and they're like, Daddy, man, you better believe that this guy would pick up his child and not hold and I'd love.

06:52.508 --> 06:55.051
That's what God wants to do for us.

06:56.974 --> 07:02.240
He wants us to boldly come into his throne room, to step into his presence.

07:02.261 --> 07:03.462
So do I have to pray?

07:04.463 --> 07:09.650
Well, in theory, no, but why wouldn't you?

07:10.978 --> 07:16.668
I don't have to eat either, but it's a good thing that I eat, right?

07:16.969 --> 07:18.972
I share with you last week, this is pretty profound.

07:19.633 --> 07:23.520
I don't need a parachute to jump out of an airplane, but it helps.

07:27.007 --> 07:31.234
Our conversation with God strengthens our relationship with Him.

07:32.436 --> 07:35.602
It gives us a confidence in Him.

07:36.098 --> 07:39.243
It releases that level of trust.

07:39.283 --> 07:42.649
It strengthens our relationship.

07:42.669 --> 07:42.869
Why?

07:43.110 --> 07:46.435
Because suddenly, I'm able to share my heart with him.

07:46.455 --> 07:57.613
I no longer am I bottling those things in, but I'm giving them to God and in return as I listen to him, because what we've discovered is prayer is as much listening as it is speaking.

07:58.936 --> 07:59.196
Right?

08:00.478 --> 08:02.802
Sometimes we're guilty of doing all the work,

08:03.970 --> 08:06.193
But God says, sometimes I just want you to be still.

08:07.395 --> 08:08.597
Just be still and listen.

08:09.879 --> 08:10.880
So do I have to pray?

08:10.920 --> 08:13.284
Well, not necessarily, but it's a good thing if you do.

08:13.764 --> 08:17.109
The second thing that we've talked about is how do I pray?

08:17.150 --> 08:20.454
We look last week of what it looks like to talk to God.

08:21.035 --> 08:26.083
What's that look like in our personal lives and how do we accomplish that task?

08:26.503 --> 08:33.714
Now these questions are often the questions that keep us from truly living a life a prayer, but there's another question that sometimes

08:33.826 --> 08:36.569
trips us up and we'll kind of bypass it.

08:36.589 --> 08:42.134
We have a plan of action and I'll talk about what we try to do in just a few moments.

08:43.035 --> 08:48.560
But here's another downfall and the question is this, how do I pray for and with others?

08:50.222 --> 08:53.185
Sometimes we're afraid to pray for others.

08:54.065 --> 08:57.689
Have you ever had one of those moments when someone says, hey, will you pray for me?

08:57.729 --> 09:02.994
And really you don't know their name, but you're supposed to know their name?

09:03.682 --> 09:08.208
And you're afraid that if you ask what their name is, now they're gonna be offended that you don't remember who they are.

09:08.228 --> 09:11.212
And you're like, I don't even know how to pray.

09:11.553 --> 09:15.739
So you're like, Lord, I pray that you'll just bless my friend.

09:15.779 --> 09:18.643
Bless this person that I'm praying.

09:18.843 --> 09:22.108
Yeah, so we kind of push back from the prayer.

09:22.468 --> 09:27.796
I wanna challenge you today, embrace that conversation with God.

09:28.737 --> 09:32.402
But this particular question is a tough question because there's a lot of layers

09:32.546 --> 09:35.710
So I want to begin to peel them back today.

09:36.511 --> 09:46.944
You see, many times if we do pray with people, we're hindering, we're pushing back because truth is told we'd rather pray alone.

09:47.044 --> 09:47.324
Why?

09:47.605 --> 09:49.126
Because we feel safer.

09:50.248 --> 09:54.313
When we pray for somebody else, what happens if I stumble on my words?

09:54.373 --> 09:56.576
What happens if I pray too loudly?

09:56.596 --> 09:58.778
What happens if I don't pray loud enough?

09:58.798 --> 10:01.842
I don't know that I've got all the fancy words to say.

10:02.338 --> 10:09.467
But praying with somebody can sometimes be intimidating, but I believe that we look at it from the wrong perspective.

10:09.487 --> 10:09.987
Here's the deal.

10:10.428 --> 10:18.418
When we pray, when we're praying for somebody else, when we're praying individually, when we're just crying out to God, here's what I want you to understand.

10:18.778 --> 10:20.540
God's not grading your prayer.

10:22.443 --> 10:26.047
He doesn't listen to your prayer and go, I'm gonna give you a C minus today.

10:26.067 --> 10:27.569
I might meet that need.

10:27.629 --> 10:31.794
That's not how God works.

10:32.834 --> 10:51.584
Praying for others is not a performance, it's not a moment to shine, it's not a moment for us to make ourselves look good, but it's an opportunity to partner together with somebody else, to walk side by side with them, to gather together the need that they have and be that support.

10:51.784 --> 10:55.289
We say it all the time at an encounter church, nobody walks alone.

10:55.530 --> 11:00.818
What greater way to walk with somebody else, but then in a moment of prayer.

11:01.122 --> 11:04.267
It's partnering together with other believers.

11:04.688 --> 11:10.698
It's a moment of inviting God into the midst of our issues and our concerns.

11:11.379 --> 11:13.001
This morning we're gonna have two texts.

11:13.021 --> 11:19.412
It's a little odd and untraditional to have two texts, but I wanna give those to you today.

11:19.432 --> 11:20.453
Number one says this.

11:20.914 --> 11:28.306
Praying the spirit at all times and on every occasion, stay alert and be persistent in your prayer for all believers

11:28.514 --> 11:29.255
everywhere.

11:29.335 --> 11:31.259
Now why do I want another text?

11:31.279 --> 11:39.353
Because sometimes we can read scriptures like this and we think, well the Bible says that I just have to pray for other people in church.

11:40.896 --> 11:42.819
Here's the problem with that mentality.

11:43.280 --> 11:49.991
Sometimes as a church it's easy to become self-absorbed into our form and no more.

11:51.013 --> 11:51.474
Come on.

11:52.162 --> 11:56.227
We're concerned about the person that sits down the row from us.

11:56.568 --> 12:00.893
We're concerned about the person that sits in the same area as us.

12:01.174 --> 12:04.919
But beyond that, that's where our level of concern stops.

12:06.541 --> 12:07.582
Well, look where the Bible says.

12:08.924 --> 12:11.808
First Timothy chapter two, I urge you.

12:12.188 --> 12:13.490
Come on, say I urge you.

12:14.370 --> 12:15.151
Why does he say that?

12:15.171 --> 12:23.343
Because it's vitally important, some translations say, so I encourage you, it's vital that some even say, I beseech thee.

12:23.383 --> 12:31.113
If you've been here very long, you know that's one of my favorite biblical words, and we don't use it at all in vocabulary, but it's a great word.

12:31.434 --> 12:34.438
I beseech you, great, great word.

12:34.798 --> 12:41.067
He says, I urge you first of all to pray for, here it is, all people.

12:42.709 --> 12:43.090
Come on.

12:43.938 --> 12:45.821
What about pastel capacitor?

12:45.921 --> 12:49.165
What about that person that I just don't like?

12:50.587 --> 12:51.809
Do I have to pray for them?

12:52.930 --> 12:53.351
Yes.

12:54.292 --> 12:58.217
What about that person at work that's a real jerk?

12:59.719 --> 13:01.702
Come on, anybody work with a jerk, don't raise your hand.

13:01.722 --> 13:02.523
This is being filmed.

13:02.563 --> 13:06.148
Do we have to pray for them?

13:07.049 --> 13:07.890
Absolutely.

13:08.450 --> 13:18.303
What about that person that's done you wrong over and over and over and over and over and over and over and over again?

13:18.364 --> 13:20.326
Yes.

13:22.569 --> 13:26.094
We got to pray for all people everywhere.

13:26.254 --> 13:26.755
Look what it says.

13:26.775 --> 13:28.638
I urge you.

13:29.298 --> 13:30.019
It's vital.

13:30.480 --> 13:35.927
I encourage you, first of all, to pray for all people.

13:36.128 --> 13:37.810
Ask God to help them.

13:39.330 --> 13:43.076
Okay, when we ask God to help them, that's not the same thing as saying God get them.

13:46.442 --> 13:49.747
That's not praying for them.

13:49.767 --> 13:52.291
We say, God, would you just speak into their lives?

13:53.934 --> 13:59.062
Lord, I know that sometimes at work they can just really be annoying, they can really be a jerk.

14:00.865 --> 14:03.730
But God, I know that there's a deeper cause.

14:04.674 --> 14:08.400
God, I don't know what their life is like on a personal level.

14:08.440 --> 14:12.646
God, I don't know what they're facing with their relationships with their finances.

14:13.568 --> 14:16.131
But Lord, I pray that you'll just intervene right where they are.

14:17.213 --> 14:18.795
Let them know that you love them.

14:20.358 --> 14:28.050
See, the Bible says that God loves everyone, that he desires that none would perish, but all would come to that place in that moment of repentance.

14:29.692 --> 14:33.618
So you begin to call their name out in prayer.

14:34.466 --> 14:38.693
Ask God to help them and intercede on their behalf.

14:38.713 --> 14:40.676
We're gonna talk about that word in just a moment.

14:40.716 --> 14:41.878
It's kind of a churchy word.

14:42.299 --> 14:46.366
Intercede on their behalf and give thanks for them.

14:47.347 --> 14:53.277
If we're truly gonna become a house of prayer, then prayer cannot stay privates.

14:54.900 --> 15:01.170
That's hard because some of us in the house, man, we would much rather just

15:01.442 --> 15:05.327
kind of go in the corner and pray privately with ourselves.

15:05.367 --> 15:14.018
Well, what happens when you're in the middle of Walmart and you find that person, you're talking to that individual, you haven't seen in a while and you say, how's it going?

15:14.098 --> 15:15.801
And they actually tell you the truth.

15:18.804 --> 15:22.109
Come on, most of you, your answer is, hey, how's it going?

15:23.430 --> 15:24.151
It's fine.

15:24.211 --> 15:25.573
It's fine.

15:26.034 --> 15:26.975
Affair to Midland.

15:27.536 --> 15:29.298
If you were kind of Southern Missouri guy.

15:30.978 --> 15:36.126
But what happens if they really begin to tell you the truth and they begin to share the difficulty?

15:36.547 --> 15:39.511
What happens if they say, man, life's not good?

15:41.354 --> 15:42.196
What do you do then?

15:43.638 --> 15:47.885
See, our greatest response should be pausing and saying, you know what?

15:48.445 --> 15:49.327
Can I pray for you?

15:51.370 --> 15:56.498
Can I just take a moment and can we agree together and have a conversation with God?

15:56.638 --> 15:58.962
We're gonna dive into this this morning.

15:59.234 --> 16:03.783
But I want you to understand the reality is that prayer cannot just be private.

16:04.745 --> 16:06.468
There's moments that it's got to be public.

16:08.031 --> 16:09.934
Let's look at five truths of public prayer.

16:10.756 --> 16:12.119
Take really good notes this morning.

16:12.139 --> 16:18.130
Number one is this, praying for others is about agreements, not eloquence.

16:19.138 --> 16:29.835
Now I feel like some of this on eloquence, I've talked about even a little bit each and every week, but I'm doing that purposely because sometimes we need to hear things more than once for it to really sink in.

16:30.757 --> 16:36.206
And some of us are afraid to pray because we're not sure that we have all the right words.

16:37.568 --> 16:38.770
Have you been there before?

16:40.873 --> 16:46.322
Have you ever had somebody ask you to pray and suddenly you thought, I don't know how to do this.

16:47.682 --> 16:51.187
What are they going to think about my prayer skills?

16:52.309 --> 16:54.492
What if I say something that's wrong?

16:55.613 --> 17:04.045
Suddenly before we even begin, we discount ourselves, we excuse our way out by saying nothing and delaying it by simply saying this to them.

17:04.065 --> 17:06.008
Well, I'll tell you what, I'll pray for you.

17:06.048 --> 17:13.298
And then lo and behold, three weeks go by and we haven't prayed for them at all.

17:14.050 --> 17:20.899
But we got out of the situation in the moment by giving that spiritual catchphrase, I'll pray for you.

17:21.620 --> 17:43.890
What would happen if in boldness, encourage, you just took them by the hands in that moment, maybe you're in the middle of Walmart, maybe you're in the middle of the Toy section or the Pharmacy or the Grocery section of Walmart and they're pouring out their heart to you or they're just saying life really stinks right now.

17:44.386 --> 17:48.873
What if you paused in the middle of Walmart and said, let's pray?

17:50.716 --> 17:51.758
What would that look like?

17:53.321 --> 17:54.863
I believe God would honor that.

17:54.903 --> 18:00.573
I believe he would honor that moment of truly praying one for another.

18:00.593 --> 18:01.294
What did Paul say?

18:01.474 --> 18:02.936
Or what did he say in 1st Timothy?

18:02.956 --> 18:03.477
We just read it.

18:03.898 --> 18:07.885
I urge you, first of all, to pray for all people.

18:08.165 --> 18:11.250
Ask God to help them.

18:13.474 --> 18:19.202
What if you simply said, let me pray for you, and then you actually do that?

18:20.624 --> 18:22.527
Matthew chapter 18 says it this way.

18:22.547 --> 18:32.882
I also tell you this, if two of you agree here on earth concerning anything you ask, my father in heaven will do it for you.

18:33.724 --> 18:40.914
For a two or three gather together as my followers, I am there among them.

18:41.890 --> 18:43.952
I love what Jesus is saying here.

18:43.972 --> 18:49.238
He truly takes the pressure off us and he places it on God.

18:49.258 --> 19:00.211
He takes a moment to emphasize not the idea of an impressive vocabulary or even a deep level of theology, but a moment of agreements.

19:00.791 --> 19:02.273
Did you see what it said in verse 20?

19:02.614 --> 19:06.578
Where two or three gathered together as my

19:07.202 --> 19:11.168
followers, some translations say in my name.

19:11.288 --> 19:12.129
What does that mean?

19:13.091 --> 19:19.179
Well, I want to take a prayer real quick, and let's back up to the very end of a prayer.

19:20.441 --> 19:29.494
If we were to pray in this moment, we would have our conversation with God, and then when we end it with a four-letter word, starting with A, it would be amen.

19:30.356 --> 19:30.576
Right?

19:30.896 --> 19:33.440
What is the word amen mean?

19:33.560 --> 19:34.802
It literally

19:34.882 --> 19:42.234
serves as the solemn affirmation of agreements with one another to God.

19:42.274 --> 19:57.299
It's not some fancy word of signing off or saying goodbye, but it's literally saying together, we agree on this, let it be, let it happen, or so be it.

19:57.900 --> 20:01.746
It's a moment of coming together in a unified purpose

20:01.890 --> 20:02.451
of faith.

20:02.491 --> 20:10.161
It's believing together that God is not only who he claims to be, but he will do what he said he will do.

20:10.222 --> 20:12.304
Let me say that again.

20:12.725 --> 20:16.851
It's not just saying, God, we believe you are who you say you are.

20:16.871 --> 20:23.140
It's saying, God, I believe that you will do what you said you will do.

20:23.260 --> 20:27.826
So when we come together as his followers or in his name,

20:29.314 --> 20:40.434
We're standing together as a unified powerhouse, a prayer, not because of who we are, but because of who He is.

20:41.538 --> 20:47.487
It's not that the two of us or the three of us or the four of us gather together.

20:47.547 --> 20:59.644
And because, hey, we have a powerhouse team here that's praying that has nothing to do with it, but it's because we petition God, the creator of the world, the one who spoke life into existence.

21:01.327 --> 21:03.870
We're saying, Lord, here we are.

21:03.910 --> 21:09.298
We're gathered together in a moment of faith

21:09.794 --> 21:17.163
we share the burdens, we release it to God, and we acknowledge that only He can meet the need.

21:18.184 --> 21:28.356
Now remember when Jesus was asked about prayer, He said, pray like this, our Father, who is in heaven, may your name be holy.

21:29.898 --> 21:33.682
In this moment, it's in agreement together, it's declaring

21:33.922 --> 21:42.156
